OL,3,CDebt collector given innocent person's
OL,4,Cdetails in mistaken identity case
OL,6,FThe parish processed the data
OL,7,F"unlawfully and without transparency",
OL,8,Ffailed to conduct proper checks to
OL,9,Fensure they had the right person, and
OL,10,Fhad an incomplete Privacy Policy, the
OL,11,Fregulator's investigation concluded.
OL,13,FThe incorrect information was then
OL,14,Fgiven to a debt collection agency to
OL,15,Ftry and reclaim unpaid taxes through a
OL,16,Fjudgement against the innocent person,
OL,17,Fbut the Jersey Office of the
OL,18,FInformation Commissioner (JOIC) says,
OL,19,F"thankfully matters did not get to
OL,20,Fthat stage".
