OL,6,FIt adds: "POG should also have had a
OL,7,Fbetter appreciation of the negative
OL,8,Fimpact being wrongly accused would
OL,9,Fhave on an individual who had done
OL,10,Fnothing wrong."
OL,12,FIn an impact statement, the regulator
OL,13,Fsays the person affected outlined the
OL,14,F"very real distress" that had been
OL,15,Fcaused by the parish's actions and
OL,16,Fstated "they had lost trust and
OL,17,Fconfidence in POG".
